Hello, All:


I'm two complaints from R CMD check in GitHub action:


https://github.com/sbgraves237/Ecfun/actions/runs/23078486810/job/67043185290


ONE says:


"Warning: bad markup (extra space?) at readDW_NOMINATE.Rd:224:31"


Rows 224:226 of readDW_NOMINATE.Rd are:


   \item{Party, Party2, Party3}{
     as described above with the argument \code{party_code}.
   }


What's wrong with this?


ALSO:


checkRd: (-1) compareOverlap.Rd:24-26: Lost braces
     24 |   Also if(\code{Plot}){
        |                       ^


Lines 24-26 of compareOverlap.Rd are in \description and read as follows:


   Also if(\code{Plot}){
     if(\code{any(is.na(dyRef))}) \code{plot(dyRef)} else \code{plot(dy)}
   }


I cannot see what's wrong with this, either.


Suggestions? Thanks, Spencer Graves

I understand that R has put Rf_findVarInFrame and R_UnboundValue on the
non-API list in order to deny direct access to PROMSXP objects.

What I can't understand is why R put R_MissingArg on the non-API list. I've
been using it to allocate functions in C, and now I'm not sure how I'm
going to get around it. Right now I would write:

SEXP formals = Rf_allocLang(1);
SET_TAG(formals, Rf_install("x"));
SETCAR (formals, R_MissingArg);
SEXP body = <...>;
SEXP env = <...>;
SEXP fun = R_mkClosure(formals, body, env);

Does anyone know how I might get around this?

